GET /api/threads

[
  {
    "parent":
    {
      "title": "Best bedtime stories thread",
      "count": 10,
      "createdAt": "2021-02-20T17:20:18.975-08:00"
    },
    "comments":
    [
      {
        "text": "Based and wholesomepilled",
        "createdAt": "2021-02-20T17:20:18.975-08:00"
      },
      {
        "text": "GME to the moon!!!:D",
        "createdAt": "2021-02-21T17:20:18.975-08:00"
      }
    ]
  }
]

Comments:
- Returns a list of threads
- Each thread contains a parent element and a comments element
- Parent fields: title (string), count (int - number of comments),
  createdAt (when the OP was created - ISO time format)
- Each comment contains two fields: text (string), createdAt (when the comment
  was created - ISO time format)
RENDER THIS (BASICALLY ALL THREADS STORED IN DB)

POST /api/threads

{
  "title": "How to get an entry level job in CS?",
  "text": "4.33 GPA, top 1 global school, 5 internships, what should I put on my resume?"
}

Comments:
- Both fields are strings
- Server will generate the timestamp
USED TO CREATE A NEW THREAD

PUT /api/threads

{
  "parentTime": "2021-02-20T17:20:18.975-08:00",
  "text": "Get a sense of humility and ask again tomorrow, nerd"
}

Comments:
- parentTime is an ISO string corresponding to the createdAt field of a thread
  (we decided to use timestamps as a primary key)
- text is a string
USED TO REPLY (CREATE A COMMENT) ON AN EXISTING THREAD
